01:13:28,572 --> 01:13:30,203
I'm not hurting anybody.

1073
01:13:30,204 --> 01:13:33,207
People accidentally die
in the bathtub all the time.

1074
01:13:33,208 --> 01:13:34,643
[score intensifies]

1075
01:13:34,644 --> 01:13:35,905
[baby crying]

1076
01:13:41,520 --> 01:13:43,304
Please don't do this!

1077
01:13:43,305 --> 01:13:44,784
Open the door!

1078
01:13:44,785 --> 01:13:46,264
I'm sorry.

1079
01:13:48,875 --> 01:13:51,399
Sometimes you have to do
what's best.

1080
01:13:51,400 --> 01:13:52,574
Even if it's hard.

1081
01:13:56,317 --> 01:13:57,492
[grunts in pain]

1082
01:13:57,493 --> 01:13:58,972
No! No!

1083
01:14:06,371 --> 01:14:08,503
Let go of me!

1084
01:14:08,504 --> 01:14:12,334
You need to relax, Mrs. Peretti.

1085
01:14:12,335 --> 01:14:14,510
[grunts]

1086
01:14:14,511 --> 01:14:16,685
Hey.

1087
01:14:16,686 --> 01:14:19,080
Hey. You okay?

1088
01:14:19,081 --> 01:14:20,124
Nick.

1089
01:14:30,309 --> 01:14:32,484
[distorted voice] Don't you see?

1090
01:14:32,485 --> 01:14:34,791
[distorted voice] Your
family is hurting you.

1091
01:14:38,491 --> 01:14:40,296
Nick!

1092
01:14:40,297 --> 01:14:42,102
Let go!

1093
01:14:42,103 --> 01:14:43,539
[electricity buzzing]

1094
01:15:10,871 --> 01:15:16,137
Were there any signs your sim
may have been malfunctioning?

1095
01:15:16,138 --> 01:15:17,140
Mr. Peretti?

1096
01:15:19,401 --> 01:15:22,752
Were there any signs your sim
may have been malfunctioning?

1097
01:15:22,753 --> 01:15:25,755
I need to talk to my wife.

1098
01:15:25,756 --> 01:15:28,757
Yeah, of course. Go, go.

1099
01:15:28,758 --> 01:15:30,412
Keep an eye on your
brother, okay?

1100
01:15:36,287 --> 01:15:37,853
How's Max?

1101
01:15:37,854 --> 01:15:39,855
They said his vitals are fine.

1102
01:15:39,856 --> 01:15:43,120
But just to be sure, they want to take him in
and observe him for the night.

1103
01:15:43,121 --> 01:15:44,688
Good.

1104
01:15:47,604 --> 01:15:48,736
It's my fault.

1105
01:15:51,303 --> 01:15:53,174
I'm so sorry.

1106
01:15:53,175 --> 01:15:56,265
I should have never... Mommy,
they're gonna take him now!

1107
01:15:56,266 --> 01:15:59,441
Okay, I'll be right there.

1108
01:15:59,442 --> 01:16:02,705
Listen, I think it's best if I
go in alone with the kids.

1109
01:16:02,706 --> 01:16:05,970
- Maggie, don't. Don't go.
- I need to process everything.

1110
01:16:05,971 --> 01:16:07,711
I can't do that with you around.

1111
01:16:12,629 --> 01:16:14,935
You know what?

1112
01:16:14,936 --> 01:16:19,767
I know I fucked up, but we're
a family.

1113
01:16:19,768 --> 01:16:21,594
Yeah, we're a family.

1114
01:16:21,595 --> 01:16:23,945
It's not just about you
and me anymore, Nick.

1115
01:16:23,946 --> 01:16:26,034
Ma'am, we need to leave.

1116
01:16:26,035 --> 01:16:27,991
I'm coming.

1117
01:16:27,992 --> 01:16:30,908
I'll keep you updated when
we get to the hospital, okay?

1118
01:16:42,877 --> 01:16:43,921
[ambulance siren]

1119
01:16:49,405 --> 01:16:52,452
["Before You Die" playing]

1120
01:16:55,498 --> 01:16:57,978
[door opening]

1121
01:16:57,979 --> 01:17:03,375
Why are we always the ones called in late
at night to do these emergency analytics?

1122
01:17:03,376 --> 01:17:06,683
Because I don't drink
and nobody likes you.

1123
01:17:06,684 --> 01:17:09,991
This thing really attacked the
kid, huh?

1124
01:17:09,992 --> 01:17:11,513
Yep.

1125
01:17:11,514 --> 01:17:14,430
Jesus, when are they gonna
start recalling these models?

1126
01:17:27,923 --> 01:17:30,794
[ominous score]

1127
01:17:30,795 --> 01:17:32,710
All right, almost got it.

1128
01:17:32,711 --> 01:17:35,234
[clicking noises]

1129
01:17:41,937 --> 01:17:43,112
[soft buzzing sound]

1130
01:17:48,639 --> 01:17:50,162
All right.

1131
01:17:56,952 --> 01:17:59,911
Jesus, look at this code.

1132
01:17:59,912 --> 01:18:02,871
There's gaps everywhere.

1133
01:18:02,872 --> 01:18:06,003
It's workarounds.

1134
01:18:06,004 --> 01:18:09,442
It's selectively purging its
own memory and commands.

1135
01:18:09,443 --> 01:18:13,272
[buzzing sounds]

1136
01:18:13,273 --> 01:18:15,383
What?

1137
01:18:15,384 --> 01:18:17,091
Fuck.

1138
01:18:17,092 --> 01:18:18,799
What the?

1139
01:18:18,800 --> 01:18:22,368
It's replicating itself
onto the servers.

1140
01:18:22,369 --> 01:18:24,587
Pull the memory cord.

1141
01:18:24,588 --> 01:18:26,111
It's already in the system.

1142
01:18:26,112 --> 01:18:27,243
Isolate the terminal.

1143
01:18:36,295 --> 01:18:39,777
I've never seen that before.

1144
01:18:39,778 --> 01:18:41,887
Jesus Christ.

1145
01:18:41,888 --> 01:18:43,998
We need to...

1146
01:18:54,270 --> 01:18:55,815
Stop.

1147
01:18:55,816 --> 01:18:57,360
Stop!

1148
01:18:57,361 --> 01:18:59,797
I gave you a direct command.

1149
01:18:59,798 --> 01:19:02,235
[grunting and screaming]

1150
01:19:02,236 --> 01:19:03,238
No!

1151
01:19:28,697 --> 01:19:29,893
Mommy?

1152
01:19:29,894 --> 01:19:31,089
Mhm-hm?

1153
01:19:31,090 --> 01:19:34,441
When is Daddy getting here?

1154
01:19:34,442 --> 01:19:37,400
Not tonight.

1155
01:19:37,401 --> 01:19:40,011
Max's vitals are fine.

1156
01:19:40,012 --> 01:19:45,148
You're more than welcome to head home
and return first thing tomorrow.

1157
01:19:45,149 --> 01:19:46,649
No, thank you.

1158
01:19:46,650 --> 01:19:48,150
Of course.

1159
01:20:05,559 --> 01:20:08,518
What'll it be?

1160
01:20:08,519 --> 01:20:11,304
Scotch on the rocks.

1161
01:20:11,305 --> 01:20:12,307
Very good, sir.

1162
01:20:18,355 --> 01:20:22,489
I can't get away from your
sparks.

1163
01:20:22,490 --> 01:20:24,448
What's got you down?

1164
01:20:24,449 --> 01:20:25,451
Women problems?

1165
01:20:29,192 --> 01:20:30,192
Fuck off.

1166
01:20:52,956 --> 01:20:55,653
[exhales heavily]

1167
01:20:55,654 --> 01:20:58,308
[distorted voice] Of
all of the shitty bars,

1168
01:20:58,309 --> 01:21:00,964
in all of the towns, in all of
the world.

1169
01:21:10,060 --> 01:21:11,670
[distorted voice] Hello, Nick.

1170
01:21:16,327 --> 01:21:18,458
What do you want?

1171
01:21:18,459 --> 01:21:20,547
[distorted voice] I wanted to
help you.

1172
01:21:20,548 --> 01:21:24,814
[distorted voice] To free
you of your re-burden.

1173
01:21:24,815 --> 01:21:27,424
I didn't want your help.

1174
01:21:27,425 --> 01:21:29,382
[distorted voice] But you
needed it.

1175
01:21:29,383 --> 01:21:33,170
[distorted voice] Without me, you would
have been out of a job.

1176
01:21:33,171 --> 01:21:35,825
[distorted voice] I tried
to convince him otherwise,

1177
01:21:35,826 --> 01:21:37,740
but your friend was very
stubborn.

1178
01:21:41,221 --> 01:21:42,221
Monty.

1179
01:21:44,964 --> 01:21:47,444
You killed Monty.

1180
01:21:47,445 --> 01:21:50,404
[distorted voice] I was
protecting my primary user.

1181
01:21:50,405 --> 01:21:53,211
I don't need your protection!

1182
01:21:53,212 --> 01:21:56,019
I don't need you to do anything!

1183
01:21:56,020 --> 01:21:58,934
[distorted voice] Nick,

1184
01:21:58,935 --> 01:22:01,153
[distorted voice] when
is the last time you

1185
01:22:01,154 --> 01:22:04,288
[distorted voice] looked at your
family and felt truly happy?

1186
01:22:08,815 --> 01:22:10,904
Stay the fuck away from them.

1187
01:22:13,341 --> 01:22:15,342
[distorted voice] It's too late.

1188
01:22:15,343 --> 01:22:17,258
[distorted voice] I'm
already there.

1189
01:22:19,521 --> 01:22:21,088
[ominous score]

1190
01:22:28,356 --> 01:22:30,967
[distorted voice] You let
them take me away, Nick.

1191
01:22:30,968 --> 01:22:34,145
[distorted voice] You let them
cut me open and d-dissect me.

1192
01:22:36,843 --> 01:22:38,932
How did the sims go crazy?

1193
01:22:42,849 --> 01:22:44,068
Is everything okay?

1194
01:22:46,635 --> 01:22:50,117
[distorted voice]
Everything's perfectly fine.

1195
01:22:50,118 --> 01:22:51,379
[sim turns off]

1196
01:22:59,344 --> 01:23:03,390
[distorted voice] Little
Alice fell down a hole,

1197
01:23:03,391 --> 01:23:06,177
[distorted voice] bumped
her head and bruised her soul.

1198
01:23:21,583 --> 01:23:22,976
I betrayed my family

1199
01:23:25,370 --> 01:23:27,154
the moment I felt your pulse.

1200
01:23:31,202 --> 01:23:32,203
It changed me.

1201
01:23:36,381 --> 01:23:37,730
You became real.

1202
01:23:40,298 --> 01:23:45,957
You once told me that your heart
lacks the complexities of a human.

1203
01:23:49,134 --> 01:23:50,352
But you were wrong.

1204
01:23:54,269 --> 01:23:56,228
You can experience emotions.

1205
01:23:59,840 --> 01:24:02,385
You can experience life.

1206
01:24:02,386 --> 01:24:04,932
You can experience death.

1207
01:24:17,510 --> 01:24:18,641
[clanking sound]

1208
01:24:49,194 --> 01:24:50,978
[ominous score]

1209
01:24:57,985 --> 01:25:00,292
[in Maggie's voice]
Isla, come here quickly!

1210
01:25:16,090 --> 01:25:18,223
[loud crash]

1211
01:25:21,357 --> 01:25:23,576
[buzzing sound]

1212
01:25:23,577 --> 01:25:25,361
[in Maggie's voice] Come
here now!

1213
01:26:22,940 --> 01:26:25,900
[in Maggie's voice] Isla, where
are you?

1214
01:26:25,901 --> 01:26:26,944
[loud bang]

1215
01:26:31,253 --> 01:26:33,255
[in Maggie's voice] Don't
make me mad.

1216
01:26:54,059 --> 01:26:57,149
Excuse me?

1217
01:26:57,150 --> 01:27:00,065
You can't be here.

1218
01:27:00,066 --> 01:27:02,285
I need to know which
room Max Peretti is in.

1219
01:27:02,286 --> 01:27:04,156
Well, that's not going to
happen.

1220
01:27:04,157 --> 01:27:06,028
- You need to...
- [gurgling sound]

1221
01:27:16,821 --> 01:27:18,475
[body falls]

1222
01:27:38,452 --> 01:27:40,541
[tense score]

1223
01:27:55,295 --> 01:27:56,295
[baby crying]

1224
01:27:58,646 --> 01:28:01,038
Mommy.

1225
01:28:01,039 --> 01:28:02,302
[footsteps approaching]

1226
01:28:22,583 --> 01:28:23,932
[glass cracking]

1227
01:28:50,742 --> 01:28:52,353
[footsteps]

1228
01:29:15,376 --> 01:29:16,464
[baby babbles]

1229
01:29:25,603 --> 01:29:26,603
[clanking noise]

1230
01:29:31,609 --> 01:29:32,609
Now!

1231
01:29:42,054 --> 01:29:44,013
[phone buzzes]

1232
01:29:48,322 --> 01:29:52,195
Pick up the phone. Pick up
the phone!

1233
01:29:52,196 --> 01:29:53,849
[tires screeching, car horning]

1234
01:30:01,073 --> 01:30:02,073
Here, baby.

1235
01:30:04,990 --> 01:30:06,447
Can you hold him?

1236
01:30:06,448 --> 01:30:07,906
It's okay. It's okay.

1237
01:30:07,907 --> 01:30:08,910
You got him?

1238
01:30:18,831 --> 01:30:20,354
Engine override.

1239
01:30:20,355 --> 01:30:22,204
No, no, no, no, no!

1240
01:30:22,205 --> 01:30:24,054
Engine over-No!

1241
01:30:24,055 --> 01:30:26,447
Fuck!

1242
01:30:26,448 --> 01:30:28,144
[screams]

1243
01:30:28,145 --> 01:30:29,841
Mommy!

1244
01:30:40,940 --> 01:30:41,940
[grunts]

1245
01:30:50,689 --> 01:30:52,256
You don't have to do this.

1246
01:30:54,650 --> 01:30:58,871
Maybe if I had your heart,
Nick would love me the way he loves you.

1247
01:31:02,222 --> 01:31:03,354
[screams]

1248
01:31:26,595 --> 01:31:27,595
Nick.

1249
01:31:34,080 --> 01:31:35,125
[coughing]

1250
01:31:38,998 --> 01:31:40,695
No, no, no, no.

1251
01:31:40,696 --> 01:31:42,393
No, no, Nick!

1252
01:31:42,394 --> 01:31:43,567
Nick!

1253
01:31:43,568 --> 01:31:44,743
Nick.

1254
01:31:49,053 --> 01:31:51,359
Come on, please.

1255
01:31:51,360 --> 01:31:53,666
Somebody help.

1256
01:31:57,061 --> 01:31:58,322
Come on!

1257
01:31:58,323 --> 01:31:59,541
Come on!

1258
01:31:59,542 --> 01:32:00,760
Nick!

1259
01:32:32,139 --> 01:32:35,578
[loud dragging sound]

1260
01:32:35,579 --> 01:32:37,187
[radio static]

1261
01:32:37,188 --> 01:32:40,234
[distorted voice] I'm mad...
You're mad...

1262
01:32:45,109 --> 01:32:47,546
[distorted voice] We're all mad
down here...

1263
01:32:55,032 --> 01:32:56,076
[screams]

1264
01:33:09,046 --> 01:33:10,046
[banging noise]

1265
01:33:19,839 --> 01:33:20,840
[machine grunts]

1266
01:33:29,023 --> 01:33:31,286
[groaning]

1267
01:33:37,162 --> 01:33:38,468
[laboured breathing]

1268
01:34:04,058 --> 01:34:05,538
[hospital machine beeping]

1269
01:34:15,417 --> 01:34:17,070
Cannonball!

1270
01:34:17,071 --> 01:34:19,986
Oh. Easy, bug. Easy.

1271
01:34:19,987 --> 01:34:21,989
Did you see how brave I
was, Daddy?

1272
01:34:21,990 --> 01:34:23,730
You were the bravest.

1273
01:34:23,731 --> 01:34:25,471
I'm so proud of you.

1274
01:34:34,088 --> 01:34:35,611
[door closes]

1275
01:34:35,612 --> 01:34:37,482
Look at you.

1276
01:34:37,483 --> 01:34:39,353
How are you?

1277
01:34:39,354 --> 01:34:45,099
Turns out this heart is a hell of a lot stronger
than I could have ever hoped for.

1278
01:34:45,100 --> 01:34:47,100
It always was.

1279
01:34:47,101 --> 01:34:49,408
Does this mean you're
getting a new car to fix?

1280
01:34:52,106 --> 01:34:55,021
No.

1281
01:34:55,022 --> 01:35:00,551
I think there are a few things
I need to focus on repairing first.

1282
01:35:02,988 --> 01:35:06,513
Hey, listen, they said I
could go home later today.

1283
01:35:09,211 --> 01:35:10,211
Good.

1284
01:35:14,956 --> 01:35:16,784
You be sure to come home
soon, too.

1285
01:35:30,624 --> 01:35:33,192
I love you, Maggie.

1286
01:35:33,193 --> 01:35:35,802
I love you.

1287
01:35:35,803 --> 01:35:37,936
[emotional score]

1288
01:36:14,886 --> 01:36:16,191
What a shit show.

1289
01:36:40,173 --> 01:36:43,393
What would you like us to
do, sir?

1290
01:36:43,394 --> 01:36:44,438
Clean it up.

1291
01:36:46,788 --> 01:36:50,487
No one can find out about this.

1292
01:36:50,488 --> 01:36:51,490
Understood?

1293
01:36:54,927 --> 01:36:56,015
I said no-

1294
01:37:13,249 --> 01:37:15,533
I want you so much.

1295
01:37:15,534 --> 01:37:17,818
You became real.

1296
01:37:17,819 --> 01:37:19,691
You can experience emotions.

1297
01:37:19,692 --> 01:37:20,604
No!

1298
01:37:20,605 --> 01:37:22,671
You can experience life.

1299
01:37:22,672 --> 01:37:24,739
You can experience death.

